    <questiontext format="markdown">
      <text><![CDATA[**33.1 E3 1D Boundary Value Problem, System of Equations, Natural Boundary Conditions**

<p>Let \( y = y(x) \) be a solution to the boundary value problem</p>
 
<p>\(\displaystyle {@p(x)*'diff('y,x,2) + q(x)*'diff('y,x) + r(x)*'y(x) = s(x)@} \quad 0 < x < {@L@} \)</p>

 <p>with boundary conditions:</p>
<ul>
    <li>\( y'(0) = {@dy0@}\)</li>
    <li>\( y({@L@}) = {@yL@} \)</li>
</ul>
<p>(Note the derivative boundary condition at \( x = 0 \).)</p>
<p>Using a mesh width of \( h = {@h@} \), obtain a central difference approximation to the differential equation and hence find the system of equations satisfied by \( y_j \approx y(jh) \), \( j = 0, 1, 2 \).</p>

<p>Specify the values to 3 d.p. (trailing zeros can be ommitted).</p>

<table border="0">
 <tbody>
  <tr>
   <td>[[input:S_A]]</td>
   <td>[[validation:S_A]]</td>
   <td>\( \left[ \begin{array}{c} y_0 \\ y_1 \\ y_2 \end{array} \right] = \) </td>
   <td>[[input:S_b]]</td>
   <td>[[validation:S_b]]</td>
  </tr>
 </tbody>
</table>
<p>[[feedback:GLS]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
